\subsection{Oppgave 4.11.2}
Vi gjør som i Eksempel 2. 
Likningssystemet kan skrives
\[
\left( \begin{array}{r} x'(t) \\ y'(t) \end{array} \right) 
= 
\left( \begin{array}{rr} 1 & 8 \\ 2 & 1 \end{array} \right) 
\left( \begin{array}{r} x(t) \\ y(t) \end{array} \right).
\]
Vi ser fort at 
\begin{itemize}
  \item Egenverdiene til $\left( \begin{array}{rr} 1 & 8 \\ 2 & 1 \end{array} \right)$ er $\lambda_1=-3$, $\lambda_2=5$,
  \item ${\bf v}_1 = \left( \begin{array}{r} -2 \\ 1 \end{array} \right)$ er en egenvektor for $\lambda_1=-3$, 
  \item ${\bf v}_2 = \left( \begin{array}{r} 2 \\ 1 \end{array} \right)$ er en egenvektor for $\lambda_2=5$. 
\end{itemize}
Den generelle løsningen av systemet er derfor 
\[
\left( \begin{array}{r} x(t) \\ y(t) \end{array} \right)
=
Ae^{-3t}\left( \begin{array}{r} -2 \\ 1 \end{array} \right) +Be^{5t}\left( \begin{array}{r} 2 \\ 1 \end{array} \right).
\]
Setter vi inn $t=0$ får vi likningssystemet 
\begin{eqnarray*}
-2A +2B &=& 1 \\
A + B   &=& 6.
\end{eqnarray*}
Løser vi dette får vi $A=\frac{11}{4},B=\frac{13}{4}$.
Den spesielle løsningen blir dermed 
\[
\left( \begin{array}{r} x(t) \\ y(t) \end{array} \right)
=
\frac{11}{4}e^{-3t}\left( \begin{array}{r} -2 \\ 1 \end{array} \right) +\frac{13}{4}e^{5t}\left( \begin{array}{r} 2 \\ 1 \end{array} \right)
=
\left(
\begin{array}{r}
-\frac{11}{2}e^{-3t} +\frac{13}{2}e^{5t}\\
\frac{11}{4}e^{-3t} +\frac{13}{4}e^{5t}
\end{array}
\right).
\]